 15:47 The N4 near Waterval Boven, which was reported closed, is now open for use. 13:00 Trac spokesperson, Solange Soares Nicholson confirmed that the road is currently closed saying that they will inform road users via their communication platforms when it is safe to use again. Until then motorists are advised to use the alternative route via the Schoemanskloof road. For more information the Trac Helpdesk can be contacted on 0800 872 264.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za